                                         "email":  "drhalilmurattasci@users.noreply.github.com",
                                         "date":  "2026-05-30T08:01:08Z"
                                     },
                       "message":  "EDITOR-SAVE-STATUS-INDICATOR: in-app bottom status bar (scene + dirty)\n\nSurface the open scene\u0027s file name + a dirty marker in an in-app bottom\nstatus bar, mirroring the OS window title (#270) but inside the editor.\nThe editor already tracked scene_source_path (#269) + a Command-Bus dirty\nflag; this renders them through the existing egui host path.\n\nInspectorSnapshot is Copy by documented invariant and a scene name is a\nnon-Copy String, so this does NOT extend it. Instead it mirrors the\ninspector stack verbatim with a separate, additive save-status channel:\n\n- editor-state: new SaveStatusSnapshot { scene_file_name, is_dirty } (Clone).\n- editor-ui: new widgets/save_status.rs — pure save_status_line() + ui().\n- editor-egui-host: new SaveStatusHandoff (verbatim InspectorHandoff copy) +\n  a bottom TopBottomPanel in EguiHost::render (additive; no signature change).\n- editor-shell: new save_status_handoff field + save_status_snapshot()\n  producer, published at the two existing per-frame publish sites.\n\nNo InspectorSnapshot / InspectorHandoff change, no EguiHost::render signature\nchange, no new crate dependency, no binary change. Dirty marker is \" *\" for\nconsistency with the window title; the empty handoff slot renders \"No scene\".\n\nTests: editor-ui formatter (7), SaveStatusHandoff (8), editor-shell producer\n(8). Canonical gate green, architecture lints 10/10.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
