                       "message":  "EDITOR-SAVE-STATUS-INDICATOR: refresh stale render-path prose (post-exec doc fix)\n\nPost-exec correction (doc-only; no runtime change). The PR added a second\nSaveStatusHandoff + a bottom status bar, but several egui-host / render-path\narchitecture comments still described the render path as inspector-only.\nUpdated:\n\n- editor-egui-host/src/lib.rs: module-doc dispatch arc (new save-status\n  bullet), deps list, EguiHost struct doc, and render() doc — now name both\n  the inspector + save-status handoffs and the bottom TopBottomPanel.\n- editor-shell/src/render_path.rs: init_render_state step list + Phase-1\n  comment + handoff-clone comment, and render_frame / render_frame_egui_only\n  docs — now describe both handoffs + the status-bar chrome.\n\nSwept the whole of both files (not just the reviewer\u0027s cited lines): also\nfixed render()\u0027s \"Future dispatches ... status bars\" sentence (no longer\nfuture) and render_frame\u0027s \"dock + Inspector chrome\" comment. Per-handoff\npublish-block comments + accessor docs correctly stay inspector-specific.\n\nNo runtime code, scope, dependency, or test change. Canonical gate green.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
